        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 2 at 12:21PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 1221 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 12 miles northeast of Clovis to 14
miles west of Milnesand, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clovis, Portales, Texico, Dora, Causey, Arch, Oasis State Park,
Pep, Lingo and Cannon Air Force Base.

This includes Highway 60 between Mile Markers 379 and 397.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
